Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Fill and boil your #kettle.

Pop the @baby spinach{100%g} into a #colander in your sink. Pour over the boiling
water from your #kettle until wilted.

Once wilted, squeeze out all of the excess water from the spinach with the back
of a #spoon. > TIP: You may need to do this in batches.

Crumble the @goat's cheese{75%g}.

Pop the @plain naans{2} onto a #baking tray{}.

Divide the @marinara sauce{120%g} between them and spread out with the back of
a #spoon, leaving a 1cm border.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{25%g} evenly over the sauce.

Top each naanizza with the spinach and goat's cheese.

Dollop on the @onion marmalade{30%g}.

When the #oven is hot, bake the naanizzas on the top shelf until the cheese is
golden and bubbling, ~{6-7%minutes}.

In the meantime, chop the @medium tomato{1} into small pieces and pop them into
a medium #bowl with the @wild rocket{20%g}.

Just before you are ready to serve, drizzle a little oil over the rocket and
tomatoes.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss gently to coat.

When the naanizzas are ready, slide them onto your #serving plates{}.

Serve the rocket salad alongside drizzled with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Enjoy!